<div id="pt-help-modal-backdrop" class="player-select-modal-backdrop"></div>
<div id="pt-help-modal" class="player-select-modal">
    <div class="player-select-modal-header">
        <h3>Perilous Trial - Help</h3>
        <button type="button" id="pt-help-close-btn" class="player-select-close-btn">&times;</button>
    </div>
    <div id="pt-help-modal-body">
        <p>This section provides leaderboards for Perilous Trial (PT) events.</p>
        <strong>Global PT Ranking</strong>
        <p>This is a server-wide ranking based on points earned from all PTs.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Points System:</strong> Points are awarded based on rank (50 for 1st, 49 for 2nd, ..., 1 for 50th).</li>
            <li><strong>All Ranks (Default):</strong> Sums up points from *all* your ranked entries across all PTs.</li>
            <li><strong>Best Rank/PT:</strong> Only your *single highest-scoring* entry for each PT is counted. This mode favors players who rank high across many different PTs, rather than ranking multiple times in the same PT.</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>Individual PTs (e.g., PT1, PT2)</strong>
        <p>This shows the specific team rankings for that single Perilous Trial.</p>
        <strong>Admin: Submitting a Team</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Select the correct PT from the dropdown.</li>
            <li>The next available rank will be suggested automatically. You can overwrite it if needed (e.g., to fix a mistake).</li>
            <li>When selecting players:
                <ul>
                    <li>If the player exists, their name will appear. You only need to fill in their new CP if it has changed.</li>
                    <li>If the player is new, you *must* provide their Class and CP. You can also assign a Guild (or create one by typing a new name).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

